                        {
                            "id": "2ff4c881",
                            "settings": {
                                "ekit_accordion_items": [
                                    {
                                        "acc_title": "What is the difference between a psychologist and a counselor?",
                                        "acc_content": "</p><p>A psychologist has a doctoral degree (Ph.D. or Psy.D.) and is trained to assess, diagnose, and treat mental health disorders, often using psychological testing. A counselor typically has a master's degree and focuses on providing support and guidance for personal, emotional, or relationship challenges.",
                                        "ekit_acc_is_active": "yes",
                                        "_id": "d032e00"
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "acc_title": "How can counseling help me improve my mental health?",
                                        "acc_content": "</p><p>Counseling provides a safe space to explore your thoughts and feelings, identify underlying issues, and develop strategies to cope with stress, anxiety, or depression. It can help you build resilience, improve relationships, and achieve personal growth.",
                                        "_id": "f105a15"
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "acc_title": "What should I expect during my first session?",
                                        "acc_content": "</p><p>Your first session is an opportunity to discuss your concerns and goals. The therapist will ask questions about your history and current challenges to understand your needs. Together, you\u2019ll create a plan for moving forward.",
                                        "_id": "a85c27f"
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "acc_title": "How many sessions will I need to see improvement?",
                                        "acc_content": "</p><p>The number of sessions varies depending on your goals and the nature of your challenges. Some clients see progress in 6\u20138 sessions, while others benefit from ongoing therapy over several months or more.",
                                        "_id": "b049ec9"
                                    },
                                    {
                                        "acc_title": "Is counseling confidential?",
                                        "acc_content": "</p><p>Yes, counseling is confidential. Therapists are bound by ethical guidelines to keep your information private. However, there are exceptions, such as if there\u2019s a risk of harm to yourself or others or legal requirements.",
                                        "_id": "bda1cb5"
                                    }
                                ],
